******
[1] Spain
Date: Fri 9 Nov 2007
From: Chris Oura (IAH-P)
<Chris.Oura@bbsrc.ac.uk>


Response to: Bluetongue - Europe (55): Spain (BTV-1, ovine), UK
(BTV-8) 20071109.3632
----------------------------------------------------------------------
We agree that the comments in Farmers weekly by Prof. Hugh Pennington
seem to indicate that _Culicoides imicola_ may be involved in BTV-8
transmission in the UK. We can assure you that this is not the case
and we have found no evidence that _C. imicola_ is present in the UK.

--
Philip Mellor, Simon Carpenter, Chris Oura
IAH Pirbright, UK.
<Chris.Oura@bbsrc.ac.uk>

[Prof. Mellor and his colleagues are gratefully acknowledged for the
above authoritative comment.

For further information on culicoides in the UK, please see the
Institute of Animal Health (Pirbright) Guide to the British
Culicoides, by John Boorman, where new species are regularly added;
available at
<http://www.iah.bbsrc.ac.uk/bluetongue/culicoides/index.html>.

For information on the vectors involved in the BTV-8 epizootic,
subscribers are referred to posting 20071030.3526 and to the paper
"Potential new Culicoides vector of bluetongue virus in northern
Europe" by R.Meiswinkel et al., The Veterinary Record, 20 Oct 2007
(available online at <http://www.ela-europe.org/read/library/BT>). - Mod. AS]

******
[2] Switzerland
Date: Fri 9 Nov 2007
Source: Web site of the Swiss Confederation [translated from German
and abridged by communicator, edited]
<http://www.news.admin.ch/dokumentation/00002/00015/?lang=de&msg-id=15565>


Bluetongue disease: update
--------------------------
A 3rd case of Bluetongue has been confirmed in Switzerland. The
cattle holding (100 animals, 1 case) is located in the Wahlen region
in the Kanton of Basel. As an additional case has been confirmed in
Germany, Rheinfelden, Baden, on the Swiss border, the existing
restriction zone has been extended covering an additional 12
municipalities in the Kanton of Aargau and adding 14 in the Kanton of Jura.

Additional information is available on the Web site of the Swiss BVET:
<http://www.bvet.admin.ch/gesundheit_tiere/01973/index.html?lang=de>.

--
