******
[3] Netherlands
Date: Fri 9 Nov 2007
Source: ANP (Netherlands national news agency) via BN DE STEM
(translated from Dutch and abridged by communicator, edited].
<http://www.bndestem.nl/binnenland/article2138005.ece>


Bluetongue costs the Dutch Livestock sector about 81 Million Euro in 2007
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Dutch farmers union LTO has presented a report today estimating
the costs for the livestock industry in the Netherlands at
approximately 81 million Euros [USD 118,762,790] for 2007.

Sheep farmers are particularly negatively affected, followed by
cattle farmers. The disease is still spreading in the Netherlands; so
far 6160 holdings have been affected.

--
Communicated by:
Sabine Zentis
Castleview Pedigree English Longhorns
Gut Laach
52385 Nideggen, Germany
